snippet: Anger from Occupy protesters over what they see as the overwhelming influence of corporate greed in politics is spilling over to both sides of the political aisle.
abstract: Anger from Occupy protesters over what they see as the overwhelming influence of corporate greed in politics is spilling over to both sides of the political aisle.
lead_paragraph: With the whole state of Iowa fixated on Republican presidential contenders just days before they go head to head in the caucuses, anger from Occupy protesters over what they see as the overwhelming influence of corporate greed in politics is spilling over to both sides of the political divide.

headline.main: Occupy Protesters Aim Anger at Both G.O.P. and Democrats in Iowa
